{
  "day": 67,
  "key": "day_67_thomas_and_belief",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "Stop Doubting and Believe"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "One of the disciples, Thomas, was not present when Jesus first appeared.",
      "He struggled to believe what the others told him."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "doubt",
        "icon": "help",
        "label": { "en": "Unless I See" },
        "lines": [
          "Thomas said,",
          "“Unless I see the nail marks in his hands",
          "and put my finger where the nails were,",
          "and put my hand into his side,",
          "I will not believe.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "appearance",
        "icon": "wb_sunny",
        "label": { "en": "Peace Be With You" },
        "lines": [
          "A week later,",
          "though the doors were locked,",
          "Jesus came and stood among them.",
          "He said,",
          "“Peace be with you.”",
          "Then he said to Thomas,",
          "“Put your finger here;",
          "see my hands.",
          "Reach out your hand",
          "and put it into my side.",
          "Stop doubting and believe.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "confession",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "My Lord and My God" },
        "lines": [
          "Thomas said to him,",
          "“My Lord and my God!”",
          "Jesus replied,",
          "“Because you have seen me,",
          "you have believed;",
          "blessed are those",
          "who have not seen",
          "and yet have believed.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Thomas asked for evidence before believing. How do you relate to his response? What does his final confession suggest about who Jesus is?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 20:24–29"]
  }
}
